Oh well. May as well go through with my plan. Znosko-Borovsky always said that a bad plan is better than no plan. If you get in the habit of planning, eventually your plans will get better. But if you never plan your moves, you'll never improve.

Up until now, I had played decently well. I was thinking about winning my Pawn back and exposing Joanne's K-side a bit. But I gave her the chance to play...

...this tactical shot, which ended the game with swift and thunderous suddenness. If I recapture the B my Q falls. No reason to drag out my resistance any longer, so I honorably resign. Well played by Joanne.
